review: Denny's with a bar. Terrible, just terrible. 2 mediocre en trees and 3 glasses of wine for $120 with tip?!?? To think we could have gone to Bob's Steak and Chophouse for the same price.

Went to cheesecake factory for deserts. I had ordered original cheesecake (classic), linda's fudge cake (amazing), and black out cake (very good). Price per slice is $7 but actually two people can easily share the slice since they are quite heavy. Surely try them if you like to have deserts after your meal.
Good food, Big servings, and very busy. Excellent place to eat during non busy times.
